# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================
# 🔐 IMPORTANT SECURITY REMINDERS:
# 
# 1. Never commit .env files to version control
# 2. Use different keys for development/staging/production
# 3. Rotate keys regularly (every 90 days recommended)
# 4. Use environment-specific values for each deployment
# 5. Keep service role keys secure - they have admin access
# 6. Monitor API key usage in respective dashboards
# 7. Set up alerts for unusual API usage patterns
# 8. Use least-privilege principle for all API keys
# 
# 🚨 NEVER SHARE THESE VALUES:
# - STRIPE_SECRET_KEY
# - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
# - SMTP_PASSWORD
# - JWT_SECRET
# - Any API secrets or private keys
#
# ✅ SAFE TO SHARE (client-side):
# - VITE_SUPABASE_URL
# - VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# - VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
# - VITE_APP_URL
# - Any VITE_ prefixed variables (they're bundled into client code)

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Update all placeholder values with your actual credentials
# 3. Configure Supabase SMTP in Dashboard > Authentication > Settings
# 4. Set up Stripe webhook endpoint: https://your-domain.com/api/stripe-webhook
# 5. Verify your domain with SendGrid for email delivery
# 6. Test all integrations in development before deploying to production